1. Sample Deployment (just the deployment, no storage yet)
text
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: sample-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: sample
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: sample
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: sample-container
          image: nginx
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80
2. PersistentVolume (PV)
Kind supports HostPath volumes for local development:

text
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolume
metadata:
  name: sample-pv
spec:
  capacity:
    storage: 1Gi
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  hostPath:
    path: /mnt/data
(The path /mnt/data should exist on all KIND nodes, or you can use any valid path on your machine)

3. PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)
text
apiVersion: v1
kind: PersistentVolumeClaim
metadata:
  name: sample-pvc
spec:
  accessModes:
    - ReadWriteOnce
  resources:
    requests:
      storage: 1Gi
4. Attach PVC to Deployment
Update your original deployment to mount the PVC:

text
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: sample-deployment
spec:
  replicas: 1
  selector:
    matchLabels:
      app: sample
  template:
    metadata:
      labels:
        app: sample
    spec:
      containers:
        - name: sample-container
          image: nginx
          ports:
            - containerPort: 80
          volumeMounts:
            - name: sample-storage
              mountPath: /usr/share/nginx/html
      volumes:
        - name: sample-storage
          persistentVolumeClaim:
            claimName: sample-pvc
Usage Sequence:

kubectl apply -f pv.yaml

kubectl apply -f pvc.yaml

kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml